## Rules of JSX

1. **Single root element** – A component must return one top‑level element. Use `<View>` or `<Fragment>` (or `<>...</>`) to wrap multiple children.

```jsx
// ❌ Wrong
return (
  <Text>Line 1</Text>
  <Text>Line 2</Text>
);

// ✅ Correct
return (
  <>
    <Text>Line 1</Text>
    <Text>Line 2</Text>
  </>
);
```

2. **All tags must be closed** – Even self‑closing tags need a slash: `<Image />` not `<Image>`.

3. **Use camelCase for attributes** – `onClick` becomes `onPress`, `class` becomes `className` (but in React Native we don't use `class` – we use `style`).
